<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880108-0181 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor: Who Was First? </HL><SO> </SO><IN> BNK </IN><TEXT>   Re your Dec. 18 news article &quot;FDIC Becomes First to Require Banks to Disclose Data on Finances to Public&quot;: Federal Credit Unions, since the inception of the Federal Credit Union in 1934, have been required to post their monthly financial statements in a conspicuous place in the lobby of their offices.    James E. Ricci   President, Educational Systems   Employees Federal Credit Union   Bladensburg, Md.</TEXT></DOC>